            <title>[KAFKA-14275] KRaft Controllers should crash after failing to apply any metadata record </title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-14275</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When replaying records on a standby controller, any error encountered will halt further processing of that batch. Currently we log an error and allow the controller to continue normal operation. In contrast a similar error on the active controller causes it to halt and exit the jvm. This is inconsistent behavior as nothing prevents a standby from eventually becoming the active controller (even when it had skipped over a record batch). We should halt the process in the case of a standby controller as well.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
